26:50.910 --> 26:52.211
What's wrong with that?

26:52.244 --> 26:54.781
DJ:
Now everyone please join
the bride and groom

26:54.814 --> 26:56.683
on the dance floor.
What's up with you tonight?

26:56.716 --> 26:57.884
You're, like, extra
snarky for no reason.

26:57.917 --> 26:59.952
Guess I'm just a bad boy.

26:59.986 --> 27:02.889
* This is the moment...
What?

27:02.922 --> 27:04.791
(sighs)

27:04.824 --> 27:07.794
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I-I'm... I'm-I'm trying...

27:07.827 --> 27:09.061
What are you trying to do?

27:09.095 --> 27:10.296
What... what is all this?

27:10.329 --> 27:12.298
You know what? You're right.

27:12.331 --> 27:14.801
Let's dance for real.

27:14.834 --> 27:17.103
Let's show off your dress.
Come on.
Oh.

27:17.136 --> 27:21.741
* This is the day
for you and I... *

27:24.343 --> 27:27.246
DJ:
And now the groomsmen have a
surprise for the special couple.

27:27.279 --> 27:29.048
There's a lot of events.
(sighs)

27:29.081 --> 27:32.084
(rhythmic percussion playing)

27:32.118 --> 27:34.186
What is this?
Oh, my God.

27:34.220 --> 27:37.423
(instrumental dance song with
Middle Eastern flavor plays)

27:38.825 --> 27:40.259
How funny is this?

27:40.292 --> 27:42.461
It's really funny.

27:42.494 --> 27:44.697
(laughs)

27:58.845 --> 28:01.380
Sorry. Tell Janice I'm sorry.

28:10.256 --> 28:12.224
Hey, multiple Aladdins!

28:12.258 --> 28:14.827
You're not really hovering!

28:14.861 --> 28:16.996
I can see your wheels!

28:29.942 --> 28:32.378
(clicking)

28:46.525 --> 28:49.461
Hoverboard dancing
is not dancing.

28:49.495 --> 28:52.198
Their feet are frozen.
Mm-hmm.

28:52.231 --> 28:56.035
You take the board away, mainly
what they're doing is leaning.

28:56.068 --> 28:58.805
It's synch... it's synchronized
leaning, basically.

28:58.838 --> 29:00.239
Yeah, well, you
couldn't do it.

29:00.272 --> 29:02.508
Yeah, well, I couldn't shake
your hand with my foot,

29:02.541 --> 29:04.510
or... but you don't want that.

29:04.543 --> 29:08.180
You're not really
making a lot of sense.

29:08.214 --> 29:10.482
Amn't I?
No. You am not.

29:10.516 --> 29:13.786
What is going on
with you, dude?

29:13.820 --> 29:15.321
What does that mean?

29:15.354 --> 29:17.523
Well, your date is
over there by herself,

29:17.556 --> 29:21.260
and you're here by yourself
getting, like, plowed.

29:23.095 --> 29:25.197
Okay.
(doorbell rings)

29:25.231 --> 29:26.532
(sighs)

29:26.565 --> 29:28.200
Put on some kind of dress.

29:28.234 --> 29:29.836
What?!
We're going
to a wedding.

29:29.869 --> 29:31.070
Have you lost your mind?

29:31.103 --> 29:33.806
Rebecca is sad.
She needs you.

29:33.840 --> 29:37.009
We're not friends anymore, okay?
And it's her fault. All right.

29:37.043 --> 29:38.811
I did everything for her.

29:38.845 --> 29:41.814
I gave her the best advice,
and she chose to ignore it.

29:41.848 --> 29:43.482
So, I mean,
I was the great friend.

29:43.515 --> 29:44.817
Oh, my God, are you serious?

29:44.851 --> 29:46.252
You think
that's what a friend is?

29:46.285 --> 29:47.486
Someone who tells you
what to do?

29:47.519 --> 29:49.088
That is not friendship.

29:49.121 --> 29:50.289
I'd never
do that to you.

29:50.322 --> 29:52.491
And, Paula,
you and I are best friends!

29:52.524 --> 29:54.827
(laughs)
What?

29:54.861 --> 29:57.096
Oh, yeah. No. Yes, we are.

29:57.129 --> 29:58.430
Yes, we are.

29:58.464 --> 30:00.366
Now go get your dress on
and let's boogie.

30:00.399 --> 30:02.368
(sighs)

30:02.401 --> 30:04.403
(crowd chatter)

30:07.306 --> 30:09.308
(sighing)

30:15.081 --> 30:16.515
You're not having the
best time, are you?

30:16.548 --> 30:18.885
I don't know
what's wrong with me.

30:18.918 --> 30:21.453
You're at a crossroads.

30:21.487 --> 30:24.556
I see that.

30:24.590 --> 30:26.993
And I think I can help.

30:27.026 --> 30:28.494
You can?

30:31.931 --> 30:34.533
This belonged
to your grandma.

30:34.566 --> 30:38.170
It would be perfect
on Valencia.

30:38.204 --> 30:40.206
Whenever you're ready.

30:40.239 --> 30:42.541
Wow! Tita Myrna,

30:42.574 --> 30:45.177
I... I don't know what to say.

30:45.211 --> 30:47.846
It's nice of you to...

30:57.589 --> 31:01.928
Wait. Did Valencia
put you up to this?

31:10.937 --> 31:12.438
I am so sorry.

31:12.471 --> 31:13.572
I am so sorry.
No, I am so sorry.

31:13.605 --> 31:15.908
This is all my fault.
It's all my fault.

31:15.942 --> 31:17.576
No, I wanted to tell you about
Greg so many times.
I should
have been a better friend.

31:17.609 --> 31:19.045
I was racked with guilt.
I should have just
listened to you.

31:19.078 --> 31:20.279
Every time I saw you, I wanted
to tell you everything.
And I felt so bad.

31:20.312 --> 31:21.447
Every time I saw your name,
I wanted to pick up the phone.

31:21.480 --> 31:23.882
I've been having so much sex.
You look like a princess.

31:23.916 --> 31:24.850
Oh, my God,
you look like a princess.
You look beautiful.

31:24.883 --> 31:25.817
You look like a sea princess
and you're, like,

31:25.851 --> 31:26.919
wearing a necklace with crabs.
I feel so bad.

31:26.953 --> 31:28.955
And I wish I'd been with you
to buy that crab necklace.

31:28.988 --> 31:30.522
I should have been better.
You're my daughter,

31:30.556 --> 31:32.591
and I should have been
a better mother.
Oh, my God,
I feel like you're my mom.

31:32.624 --> 31:34.927
So I just thought this was
gonna be mine and Greg's

31:34.961 --> 31:36.195
romantic evening,
and, oh, I'm sorry.

31:36.228 --> 31:37.463
I know you don't want
to hear about this.

31:37.496 --> 31:41.367
Hey, I'm not telling you what to
do anymore. I am done with that.

31:42.634 --> 31:44.937
But if you really like Greg,
you should tell him right away.

31:44.971 --> 31:45.938
I mean, don't waste
a single second.

31:45.972 --> 31:47.339
I'm sorry, that was advice-y.

31:47.373 --> 31:48.975
No, it's okay, I liked it.

31:49.008 --> 31:50.542
Thank you.

31:53.379 --> 31:54.613
I love you, Paula.

31:54.646 --> 31:57.616
I love you, too.

31:57.649 --> 31:59.285
Okay, you called my aunt

31:59.318 --> 32:01.387
and asked her to bring
a family heirloom

32:01.420 --> 32:03.990
to my sister's wedding
without asking me?

32:04.023 --> 32:06.625
Well, I knew she had it
and would love to give it to us

32:06.658 --> 32:09.095
and I wanted to get it
before your cousin Ruby.

32:09.128 --> 32:11.297
Oh, my God, Valencia!

32:11.330 --> 32:13.232
You didn't have any faith in me.

32:13.265 --> 32:16.235
Y-You couldn't trust me
with this one thing.

32:16.268 --> 32:18.304
I just asked for
a little time, that's all.

32:18.337 --> 32:19.538
A little time, I see.

32:19.571 --> 32:21.974
Because 15 years
isn't enough time.

32:22.008 --> 32:24.376
I was looking.
For rings.

32:24.410 --> 32:25.544
And did you buy one?

32:28.014 --> 32:30.582
You know what,
I have been patient.

32:30.616 --> 32:33.152
I have been patient through
college and through New York

32:33.185 --> 32:35.654
and through all of our friends
getting engaged

32:35.687 --> 32:37.589
and married and I was patient

32:37.623 --> 32:39.491
when you cheated on me
with Rebecca.

32:42.028 --> 32:43.695
The reason I asked for that ring
is because, deep down,

32:43.729 --> 32:46.532
I didn't believe
you were gonna do it.

32:46.565 --> 32:48.100
Were you going to?

32:50.502 --> 32:52.304
You have a ring.

32:52.338 --> 32:54.206
In your hand.

32:54.240 --> 32:56.342
You said that you were ready
for the next step,

32:56.375 --> 32:58.144
so let's do it.

32:58.177 --> 33:00.712
Let's take that ring
and get up on the bandstand

33:00.746 --> 33:03.582
and steal some wedding thunder
and get engaged right now.

33:03.615 --> 33:05.417
(scoffs)

33:05.451 --> 33:07.519
You're not listening to me.

33:10.589 --> 33:13.425
You never listen to me.
You...

33:13.459 --> 33:16.728
You pretend to, but...

33:16.762 --> 33:18.330
you never do.

33:18.364 --> 33:20.432
You know,

33:20.466 --> 33:22.168
for the last few months

33:22.201 --> 33:25.037
I thought Rebecca Bunch
was our problem.

33:25.071 --> 33:27.039
But it's not.

33:27.073 --> 33:28.407
It's you.

33:30.409 --> 33:33.412
I'm done, Josh.
We're over. For good.

33:38.284 --> 33:40.719
Hey. Hey, I want
to talk to you.

33:40.752 --> 33:43.389
So...

33:43.422 --> 33:46.258
tonight's gotten...
pretty off track.

33:46.292 --> 33:50.062
Like, this isn't us.
This isn't how we are.

33:50.096 --> 33:53.265
And... and I think
it's my fault.

33:53.299 --> 33:55.401
Yeah, because I had
an artificial view

33:55.434 --> 33:57.103
of how I wanted
this night to go.

33:57.136 --> 34:00.206
No, it's my fault.
It's my fault. It's my fault.

34:00.239 --> 34:02.208
I should not have
worn sneakers tonight.

34:02.241 --> 34:05.111
Justin Timberlake
wore sneakers with a suit

34:05.144 --> 34:07.513
and I thought I was cool,
but I'm no JTimbo.

34:09.715 --> 34:12.217
You're hilariously wasted.

34:12.251 --> 34:13.752
I know

34:13.784 --> 34:16.222
what you want to say to me.

34:16.255 --> 34:18.257
You want to break up with me.

34:25.496 --> 34:28.367
Break up with you? Oh, my...

34:28.400 --> 34:30.136
No. Greg, okay.

34:30.168 --> 34:32.271
Listen...

34:32.304 --> 34:35.607
this, like, this emotion stuff
can be scary.

34:35.641 --> 34:38.476
My parents split up
when I was little,

34:38.510 --> 34:42.148
your mom left, we don't have
the greatest role models here.

34:42.181 --> 34:44.783
But there's been something

34:44.815 --> 34:47.219
I've been wanting
to tell you all night.

34:47.253 --> 34:49.788
And even though
it scares me to death,

34:49.821 --> 34:51.790
I'm gonna be brave.

34:51.822 --> 34:54.426
So, uh,

34:54.460 --> 34:57.896
even though we've only been
seeing each other

34:57.929 --> 34:59.798
for a short time...

34:59.831 --> 35:01.767
I, um...

35:01.800 --> 35:04.370
I care about you.

35:04.403 --> 35:08.340
Like, a lot.

35:18.284 --> 35:20.252
So, tell me...

35:20.286 --> 35:23.255
tell me how you feel.
If you have any feelings. And...

35:23.289 --> 35:25.257
I don't care how you tell me,
Greg, okay?

35:25.291 --> 35:27.326
I don't care if you fart
while you're saying it,

35:27.359 --> 35:29.428
just please tell me.

35:38.770 --> 35:41.173
Can you say something?

35:41.207 --> 35:42.541
Okay.

35:42.574 --> 35:45.877
I... think...

35:47.713 --> 35:49.448
...you're cool.

35:49.481 --> 35:52.218
You...

35:52.251 --> 35:54.220
Sorry, after, like,
everything we've been through,

35:54.253 --> 35:56.355
you just, you just
think I'm cool?

35:56.388 --> 35:58.724
Yeah. I think...

35:58.757 --> 36:00.826
we have fun together, yeah.

36:00.859 --> 36:03.429
But let's not...

36:03.462 --> 36:06.298
like, plan out our future.

36:06.332 --> 36:08.634
Let's just focus on, um...

36:08.667 --> 36:10.669
on tonight and have fun, okay?

36:12.538 --> 36:14.373
Wait, what?

36:17.509 --> 36:20.912
Uh, but right now
I, um...

36:20.946 --> 36:23.882
I need to-- I need to take a--
I need to take a nap.

36:25.016 --> 36:27.453
Greg?

36:27.486 --> 36:31.590
Greg? Hey.
Hey, Greg?

36:31.623 --> 36:34.593
Ah, yes, the classic
Serrano pass-out.

36:34.626 --> 36:36.395
I'll get him
an Uber.

36:36.428 --> 36:37.729
Um, yeah, and I'll go with you.

36:37.763 --> 36:39.731
No, you will not. You stay here.
You don't want to see

36:39.765 --> 36:41.333
what's on the other side
of this.

36:41.367 --> 36:42.634
War movie.

36:45.371 --> 36:47.506
I'm sorry he blew it.

36:47.539 --> 36:50.242
I know that
he cares, but...

36:50.276 --> 36:52.544
it's Greg,
it's just who he is.

37:00.419 --> 37:02.354
Hey, everybody,
time to get inside.

37:02.388 --> 37:03.555
Aunt Myrna's going to sing.

37:03.589 --> 37:04.790
(applause)

37:04.823 --> 37:08.694
DJ:
Ladies and gentlemen,
Aunt Myrna.

37:09.861 --> 37:12.531
Oh, my gosh.
Oh, hello, everyone.

37:12.564 --> 37:15.033
I would like to
dedicate this song

37:15.066 --> 37:16.635
to Jayma

37:16.668 --> 37:18.804
and Phillip. You may
already know this one.

37:18.837 --> 37:22.574
I sang this on Star Search
in 1984

37:22.608 --> 37:25.944
and I got 3 3/4 stars.

37:25.977 --> 37:29.548
She's just the worst.

